<br>
35 add, 5.5 spd: 32.5 avg damage/hit<br>
46 add, 5.5 spd (calculated): 32.5*(7/5)=45.5<br>
Difference: 13 <br>
<br>
So with the 46 add, using a 5.5 spd weapon, we can expect a difference of 13 damage/hit.<br>
<br>
Now I'll look at the average damage from the first post Mance (50 natural axe spec) did vs yellow cave trows. He is using a 5.3 spd War Cleaver. <br>
<br>
Avg damage, including crits and styles: 266.5<br>
<br>
Having 44 rather than 46 songs will allow you 2 more points in weapon spec. If your total spec is below 50 (highly unlikely due to items and RR) you will gain 1.5% damage per point. Based on Mance's damage, 2 weapon spec gains a total of 8 dmg/hit with a 5.3 spd weapon. Using 5.5 spd weapon this would be about 8.3 dmg/hit.<br>
<br>
More likely, you will be above 50 with items. That only gives you &lt;1% per spec point. If we assume 1%, and that's being generous, you only gain 5.5 dmg/hit.<br>
<br>
<br>
To conclude, 46 songs gets you 13 more damage/hit from the add while sacrificing only 8.3 damage/hit at best. This doesn't even take groups in to account. Admitedly, this isn't exact but the difference is large enough that I think 46 songs is CLEARLY better than 44. <br>
<br>
